node.text: Continuing through our 10 year anniversary journey, I wanted to talk about what I think the purpose of classroom decor is. You definitely don’t need it to be an amazing teacher! The joy of teaching will always be in your heart!  However, decor can help bring joy when you feel good in your environment whether it’s one bulletin board you are proud of OR the way your entire room flows. It can help you stay organized and enhance teaching in a fun and purposeful way. Listen in as I share my thoughts on this topic. 🥰 #classroomdecor #schoolgirlstyle

node.title: How classroom decor can bring joy❣️

node.text: When I create a collection, sometimes there’s a strong message behind the design.  With this collection, daisies symbolize new beginnings.  This was PERFECT for my very first theme 10 years ago and oddly, it feels very fitting for the stage of life  I’m in right now.  Whether you are going back to your classroom after a very hard 2020, or maybe you are a new teacher just starting out, or maybe you are experiencing beautiful new beginnings in your personal life, this collection could be just the message you are looking for. ❤️#classroomdecor #daisycollection #oopsadaisy #newbeginnings

node.text:
A breakdown of how I created the “You Are My Sunshine” poster from our Boho Rainbow classroom makeover for @raissa_elisabet. This makeover was for a Middle School Math room. I took the Boho Rainbow Sunshine cut-out to Staples and had them enlarge it and print it on a 24”x36” sheet of paper. I cut it out and secured it to the cinderblock walls with my favorite mavalus tape. I used twine to give the illusion that it was hanging, and then hot glued a paper wooden bead (from the Better Together door decor set) to the top of it. The best part about this cut-out is you can print this out at any size that fits in your space best! 
PRO TIP! The key to getting this at a reasonable price is to ask for it to be printed on blueprint paper.👌🏻 ☀️ 
#bohorainbow #youaremysunshine #classroomdecor #schoolgirlstyle #classroommakeover

Thank you to everyone for supporting Schoolgirl Style over the last ten years! 🤗🤗🤗
As our 10 year anniversary celebration comes to a close, I just want you to know how grateful I am to be in your classrooms! Being a teacher is one of the hardest jobs there is, and I will forever give back to the profession that changed my life. 
I also want to say thank you to the teacher stores that took a chance on me and believed in me all of those years ago. I am so excited for the future. The best is yet to come!!! 
#grateful #10yearsofsgs #schoolgirlstyle #classroomdecor #celebratelearning
